I'm using GIMP 2.10.10 on Windows 10 and trying to use the Invert tool with Free Select Tool still results in a silent crash.  To be clear, OpenCL is NOT enabled in my preferences (and it crashes regardless of it being enabled or not - I tried both).  I'm using a Dell G5 15 5587 laptop with Nvidia Optimus (Intel Graphics 630 Core i5 paired with an Nvidia 1060 "MaxQ") using an external monitor via HDMI.

I'll attach the file I'm editing. It'll work whether it's the XCF or the original PNG so I'm just uploading the XCF with the area already selected. I've selected the area there near the middle of the texture, the idea is to use invert to make it light colored, then colorize to change the color.

[RD_thigh_boot_red_thigh_strap1.xcf](/uploads/0b690961b4097de02db5aae08c3aba08/RD_thigh_boot_red_thigh_strap1.xcf)

The xcf should have the area in question preselected.

Extra note:  I tried the same functions in sequence with 2.10.8 and free select then invert works as it's supposed to.

